# Backend Conventions

## Stack
- Node.js + Express, PostgreSQL (production) / SQLite (local dev)
- Stripe for payments, Resend for transactional emails
- Session-based auth (express-session) with bcrypt PIN hashing

## Database
- Query wrappers: `query()`, `queryOne()`, `execute()` from `config/database.js`
- Use `$1, $2` parameterized placeholders (PostgreSQL style); the wrapper auto-converts for SQLite
- `initConnection()` must be called before queries (handled by server startup; standalone scripts use `pg.Pool` directly)
- Tables: `users`, `orders`, `addons`, `products`, `admins`, `email_logs`, `ebook.download_events`

## Auth
- User auth: email + OTP or PIN (4-digit bcrypt hash in `users.pin_hash`)
- Admin auth: `requireAdmin` middleware checks `req.session.adminId`
- User auth: `requireAuth` middleware checks `req.session.userId`

## Orders
- `orders.new_addons` and `orders.shipping_address` are JSON strings
- `payment_status` values: `pending`, `card_saved`, `succeeded`, `charged`, `charge_failed`
- `paid` column: `0` (unpaid) or `1` (paid)
- Shipping calculated via `calculateShipping(country, cartItems)` using zone-based rates from `config/shipping-rates.js`
- Prices validated server-side via `validateCartPrices(cartItems, isBacker)`

## Backer Types
- `pledged_status`: `pledged`, `collected`, `dropped`
- Dropped backers are charged immediately (PaymentIntent); regular backers save card (SetupIntent)
- Indian users always charged immediately (RBI regulations)
- `is_late_pledge` flag: user pays retail instead of backer prices

## Conventions
- Helper functions go in `utils/helpers.js` and are exported via `module.exports`
- Email sending via `services/emailService.js` (Resend API)
- Admin routes in `routes/admin.js`, prefixed with `/api/admin/`
- Standalone scripts in `utility/` connect to DB directly via `pg.Pool`
